 </sub> is the moving average parameter at temporal lag 
 <italic>k</italic> and spatial lag 
 <italic>l</italic>; 
 <italic>W</italic>
 <sup>
  <italic>(t)</italic>
 </sup> is the 
 <italic>N×N</italic> matrix of weights for spatial order 
 <italic>l</italic>; and 
 <italic>Ɛ(t)</italic> is the random normally distributed error vector at time 
 <italic>t</italic> [
 <xref rid="pone.0207518.ref051" ref-type="bibr">51</xref>].
